The 9th edition of the Africa International Film Festival (AFRIFF) opened on Sunday, November 10, and in attendance was the Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed, who delivered a speech to guests. Filmmakers, producers and actors were also in attendance, including Tope Oshin, Ini Edo, Nse Ike Etim, Kate Henshaw and John Njamah, all of whom were there to see the opening film, Waad Al Kateab and Edward Watt’s multiple award winning “For Sama.” See photos from the event:   The post Lai Mohammed, Ini Edo, Nse Ike Etim attend the Opening Night of #AFRIFF2019 appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija Nollywood classic Living in Bondage is back with a sequel tagged Breaking Free that premiered Saturday night. The theme of the star-studded event was “Demons in Diamonds” and of course, the guests attended the bash at the Film House Cinema in Lekki with the goal of nailing it. With a fleet of shimmer… November 4, 2019 In "Entertainment" …as Nse Ikpe Etim hosts AMAA show Shina Peters, Paul Play Dairo, others to perform TONIGHT, the city of excellence, Lagos and  indeed, Africa will stand still as the 13th  edition of the annual African Movie Academy Awards,AMAA, holds amid glitz and glory,at the Convention Centre of the Eko Hotel,… July 14, 2017 In "News" Art X Lagos began last night and somehow it managed to top all the excitement we had prior to the event. Hard to believe, but leave it to the incredible Art X Lagos team to beat all of Lagos’ collective imagination. The venue, Civic Centre was filled to capacity with… November 4, 2017 In "News"